<body class="ignore-math">
<article class="exercise exercise-like"><h3 class="heading">
<span class="type">Checkpoint</span><span class="space"> </span><span class="codenumber">1.8</span><span class="period">.</span>
</h3>
<article class="task exercise-like"><h4 class="heading"><span class="codenumber">(a)</span></h4>
<p>Use Newton's Third Law, (<span class="process-math">\(F\)</span>)orce=(<span class="process-math">\(m\)</span>)ass<span class="process-math">\(\cdot\)</span> (<span class="process-math">\(a\)</span>)cceleration to show that</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
m\dfdx{v}{t}=(m-m_w)g-Rv,
\end{equation*}
</div>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
v(0)=v_0
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p>Let <span class="process-math">\(M=m-m_w\)</span> and note that <span class="process-math">\(M\gt0\)</span> (why?). Show that the above leads to the differential equation</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
\frac{\dx{v}}{Rv-Mg}=\frac{-1}{m}\dx{t}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
v(0)=v_0.
\end{equation*}
</div></article><article class="task exercise-like"><h4 class="heading"><span class="codenumber">(b)</span></h4>
<p>Use the substitution <span class="process-math">\(z=Rv-Mg\text{,}\)</span> to rewrite the above equation as</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
\frac{\frac{1}{R}\dx{z}}{z}=-\frac{1}{m}\dx{t}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p class="continuation">and show that</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
v=\frac{Mg}{R}+\left(v_0-\frac{Mg}{R}\right)e^{-\frac{r}{m}t}.
\end{equation*}
</div></article><article class="task exercise-like"><h4 class="heading"><span class="codenumber">(c)</span></h4>
<p>Compute <span class="process-math">\(v\text{.}\)</span> This will be the terminal velocity of the sand settling in the water. Notice that this should be independent of <span class="process-math">\(v_0\text{.}\)</span> How does your answer for terminal velocity depend on <span class="process-math">\(M=m-m_w\)</span> and <span class="process-math">\(R\text{?}\)</span> Does this make sense physically?</p></article></article><span class="incontext"><a href="section-4.html#exercise-2" class="internal">in-context</a></span>
</body>
